What does this program print?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

void safe() noexcept {}
void risky() {}

int main() {
    std::cout << std::boolalpha;
    std::cout << noexcept(safe()) << "\n";
    std::cout << noexcept(risky()) << "\n";
    std::cout << noexcept(1 + 2) << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```

This swap function is supposed to be `noexcept` but has a subtle issue. What is the bug?

```cpp
#include <string>

void swap_strings(std::string& a, std::string& b) noexcept {
    std::string tmp = a; // copy
    a = b;
    b = tmp;
}
```

